  "instructions": [
    "Heat sesame oil in a wok or large frying pan over medium heat.",
    "Add minced garlic, ginger, and red pepper flakes. Stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Add squid to the wok. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until squid turns opaque (about 2-3 minutes).",
    "Stir in chili garlic paste if using. Cook for an additional minute to enhance flavor.",
    "Mix soy sauce, rice vinegar, and toasted bread crumbs together. Pour into the wok with the cooked squid.",
    "Continue stirring until all ingredients are fully incorporated and heated through (about 2-3 minutes).",
    "Serve hot as a snack or accompaniment to your meal."
